Our Pacific roots remind us that creativity is a gift, excellence is a responsibility, and progress is something we achieve together. We design with heart, we act with intention, and we always move forward as one — with our clients, our teams, and the people we serve.', 'Full Interior Design Service', 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/logos/nest.jpg', 'https://nestinteriors.co.nz', 'studio@nestinteriors.co.nz', '021 167 1027', '593 Te Rapa Road, Level 1, Mayfair Business Centre', 'New Zealand', 'Consulting & Professional Services', 'active', 'verified', NULL, NULL, '2025-12-11 22:05:48.010308+00', '2026-03-05 02:35:18.829614+00', '2026-02-26', 'Tonga Robertson', '{English}', '{"facebook": "https://facebook.com/NESTinteriorsanddesign", "linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/company/nest-interiors-design", "instagram": "https://instagram.com/nest_interiors_nz"}', NULL, 'Hamilton', 'Hamilton', '3200', NULL, 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/banners/Nest.png', 'Tonga', false, NULL, NULL, 'nest-interiors', false, NULL, NULL, true, 'homepage'),
	('6bd8fad1-df64-4c3c-8cd8-7cb63be2926a', 'Anarra Alofa Est.2020', 'Talofa lava, my name is Sharon, co-founder and owner of Anarra Alofa.
My creative journey began in 2020, when I first set my heart on making handcrafted board signs. Shortly after, I welcomed my first child — my son — and, like many mothers, I placed that dream on hold. Even so, the desire to create never left me.

Over time, my inspiration naturally returned through Sei — the floral ear pieces deeply loved and worn by Samoan women. In our culture, Sei are more than adornment; they are expressions of beauty, identity, and pride. The idea of creating them stayed with me, quietly growing until the time felt right.

At the beginning of last year, I finally took the step to bring Anarra Alofa to life. Starting small and working with minimal materials, I began handcrafting Sei with love, care, and intention. What started as a simple creative outlet has grown into a heartfelt small business rooted in culture, creativity, and passion.

Anarra Alofa is a reflection of my journey — as a mother, a Samoan woman, and a creator — and a celebration of the beauty we carry and share through our culture.', 'Elevate your style with beautifully crafted Sei''s for every occasion at Anarra Alofa.', 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/logos/anarraalofa.jpg', NULL, 'sharonnaseri@gmail.com', '+64212170344', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'Arts & Culture', 'active', 'verified', NULL, NULL, '2026-01-06 22:28:48.12743+00', '2026-03-05 02:35:18.829614+00', '2026-02-26', 'Sharon Naseri', '{English}', '{"tiktok": "https://tiktok.com/@anarraalofa2020", "facebook": "https://facebook.com/silaumea.ieru", "instagram": "https://instagram.com/anarraalofa2125"}', NULL, 'Auckland', NULL, NULL, 'Monday-Friday 9am-5pm', 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/banners/Anarra%20Alofa.png', 'Samoa', false, NULL, NULL, 'anarra-alofa-est-2020', false, NULL, NULL, true, 'homepage'),
