	('525e84f2-66d3-4a1b-a896-dd64d01ec033', 'Tuhono Design', 'Tuhono Design was created by Jay and Sarah, a proud Maori whanau dedicated to revitalising te reo Maori in everyday spaces. Inspired by their own journeys of reconnecting with their heritage, they design bilingual planners, calendars, prints, and educational resources that make Maori language and culture accessible, beautiful, and part of daily life. Their kaupapa is built on whanaungatanga, kotahitanga, and uplifting the next generation so they can grow up confident in their identity. Through thoughtfully crafted products rooted in meaning and connection, Tuhono Design invites whanau everywhere to learn, speak, and live te reo Maori with pride.', 'Bilingual Maori Resources to Inspire, Learn & Connect', 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/logos/tuhono.jpg', 'https://tuhonodesign.com', 'kiaora@tuhonodesign.com', NULL, NULL, 'New Zealand', 'Arts & Culture', 'active', 'verified', NULL, NULL, '2025-12-12 18:28:30.64805+00', '2026-03-05 02:35:18.829614+00', '2026-02-26', 'Sarah', '{"Te Reo Māori",English}', '{"tiktok": "https://tiktok.com/@tuhonodesign", "facebook": "https://facebook.com/Tuhonodesign"}', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'New Zealand', NULL, NULL, 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/banners/Tuhono.png', 'New Zealand Māori', false, NULL, NULL, 'tuhono-design', false, NULL, NULL, true, 'homepage'),
	('fcb997d1-fb71-4406-b902-cc5ef3208b03', 'Papua New Guinea Bilums and Baskets', 'Papua New Guinea Bilums & Baskets, run by CJ & LJ Mountford and based in Bundaberg, Queensland, is a small family business dedicated to sharing authentic Papua New Guinea arts and crafts with the wider community.

Specialising in traditional bilums and handwoven baskets, each piece is created using techniques passed down through generations. Bilums are traditionally crafted by women, woven in a variety of shapes and sizes to serve different purposes — from everyday use to baby carrying. The baskets are traditionally crafted by men, reflecting distinct cultural roles and knowledge systems.

Only three provinces in Papua New Guinea continue this specific weaving tradition:

North Solomon (Buka)
Southern Highlands
Eastern Highlands

These handcrafted pieces are both functional and meaningful, suitable for home décor, shopping, picnics, and baby carrying — while carrying the stories, skills, and heritage of the communities who make them.

By supporting Papua New Guinea Bilums & Baskets, you are helping preserve traditional knowledge and create income opportunities for PNG artisans.', 'CJ & LJ Mountford', 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/logos/pngbilum.jpg', NULL, 'Cmford@southernphone.com.au', '0423 819 378', NULL, 'Australia', 'Arts & Culture', 'active', 'verified', NULL, NULL, '2025-12-17 06:11:26.868237+00', '2026-03-05 02:35:18.829614+00', '2026-02-26', 'Linah Mountford', '{Pidgin,English}', '{"facebook": "https://facebook.com/PapuaNewGuineaBilumsAndBasketsCjLjMountford", "instagram": "https://instagram.com/pngbilumsnbaskets"}', NULL, 'Bundaberg', 'Queensland', NULL, '10am to 2pm', 'https://mnmisjprswpuvcojnbip.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/admin-listings/banners/PNG%20Bilums.png', 'Papua New Guinea', false, NULL, NULL, 'papua-new-guinea-bilums-and-baskets', false, NULL, NULL, true, 'homepage'),
	('a1fb7177-900d-41f8-b635-c155a16c2e43', 'L''ame Du Pareu by Vai''ohani', 'Discover the magic of pareo art with Vaihere in beautiful Raiatea. In this hands-on workshop, you''ll learn the traditional craft of painting your own pareo, using colours and patterns that reflect your personal story.

Choose from three experience levels:
🎨 Child''s Pareo (3 hrs) — A fun, creative session perfect for young artists.
🎨 Guided Design (3 hrs) — Vaihere sketches your chosen idea, and you bring it to life with paint.
🎨 Create Your Own (4 hrs) — Design and paint your own pareo from scratch.

All materials are included — just bring yourself and your creativity, and leave with a beautiful handmade pareo to take home. A meaningful and memorable activity for both locals and visitors.

