s in Papua New Guinea continue this specific weaving tradition:\r\n\r\nNorth Solomon (Buka)\r\nSouthern Highlands\r\nEastern Highlands\r\n\r\nThese handcrafted pieces are both functional and meaningful, suitable for home décor, shopping, picnics, and baby carrying — while carrying the stories, skills, and heritage of the communities who make them.\r\n\r\nBy supporting Papua New Guinea Bilums & Baskets, you are helping preserve traditional knowledge and create income opportunities for PNG artisans.", "postal_code": null, "contact_name": "Linah Mountford", "created_date": "2026-02-26", "social_links": {"facebook": "https://facebook.com/PapuaNewGuineaBilumsAndBasketsCjLjMountford", "instagram": "https://instagram.com/pngbilumsnbaskets"}, "state_region": "Queensland", "contact_email": "Cmford@southernphone.com.au", "contact_phone": "0423 819 378", "business_hours": "10am to 2pm", "contact_website": null, "languages_spoken": ["Pidgin"], "cultural_identity": "Papua New Guinean", "short_description": "CJ & LJ Mountford", "subscription_tier": "featured", "stripe_customer_id": null}', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2026-02-26 21:23:29.160834+00'),
